"3:13:18" : {s: 3, a: 13, w: 18, r: "عين", t: "ٱلْعَيْنِ", l: "عَيْن", lc: 57, tl: "l-ʿayni", lb: "চোখ",e: "(of) their eyes", b: "চোখের", i: "mata", f: 1, rm: "to hurt in the eye, smite anyone with the evil eye, flow tears, become a spy. Aayan - to view, face. Ainun - eye, look, hole, but of a tree, spy, middle letter of a trilateral word, spring of water, chief, personage of a place. Ayan (pl. Inun): lovely, wide-eyed, lovely black eyed. Maiinun - water, spring."},
